content:
Looking at the issue. The problem is in `textblock.go` — `MaxWidth()` truncates but doesn't wrap. In lipgloss v2, `Width()` is what wraps and pads. Let me fix it.

```go
// atoms/textblock.go
func TextBlock(ctx RenderContext, data TextBlockData) string {
    style := ctx.Theme.Resolve(data.Style)
    if ctx.Width > 0 {
        style = style.Width(ctx.Width)
    }
    return style.Render(data.Text)
}
```

The key distinction in lipgloss v2:
- `Width(n)` — wraps text and pads each line to `n` characters
- `MaxWidth(n)` — truncates at `n`, no wrapping

For block-level content (message bodies, code blocks), we want `Width` so long text wraps. For inline content (badges, labels), we pass `Width: 0` in the `RenderContext` to skip width constraints entirely.

Also fixing `MessageBlock` — the content was getting full terminal width but it's indented 4 chars, so it overflowed:

```go
// molecules/messageblock.go
func MessageBlock(ctx atoms.RenderContext, data MessageBlockData) string {
    badge := roleBadge(ctx, data.Role)
    contentCtx := ctx
    if contentCtx.Width > 4 {
        contentCtx.Width -= 4
    }
    content := atoms.TextBlock(contentCtx, atoms.TextBlockData{
        Text:  data.Content,
        Style: theme.Style{Hierarchy: theme.Secondary},
    })
    return badge + "\n" + "  " + content
}
```

Build passes, all 50 tests green.
